objects.title: Settings
objects.text: Options that affect the CYOA itself.

objects.title: Character
objects.text: Personal details.

objects.title: Races
objects.text: Species options.

objects.title: Progress
objects.text: How far you have climbed.

objects.title: Drop-In
objects.text: It looks like you are keeping your own body and will brave the tower as you are. Be careful who you share your secret with.

objects.title: Reincarnation
objects.text: You will be leaving your old body behind to take one specially provided for your new adventure.

objects.title: Towerborn
objects.text: You originate from inside the Tower on one of its many floors. Even if you are born in the tower, Headon may overlook you if you lack the potential to climb the tower or play into one of his many schemes.

objects.title: Irregular
objects.text: You originate from outside the Tower. It is uncertain how you managed to get inside the Tower, but you will find yourself before Headon on the First Floor where he will determine your potential to climb the tower. This option places you in the same category as Rachel to Baam, or the Family Heads to Zahard.

objects.title: Chosen Irregular
objects.text: There is no doubt about it; you entered the Tower under your own power. Fate will conspire to see your success as you climb the Tower. It is no longer required for you to enter the Tower on the First Floor, though you will have to begin your climb on the Second if you choose to accept Headon's offer. One day you will join the other monsters that have graced the Tower such as Urek, Zahard, and Enryu. Until then, Baam may become a healthy rival or dangerous adversary.

rows.title: Apparent Age
rows.titleText: Your real age isn't as important as how you're perceived based on your apparent age. Young or old, you can still climb the Tower. Your apparent age is linked to your personality/mental age.

rows.title: Races
rows.titleText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.

rows.title: Progress
rows.titleText: Choose where you are in your climb to the top.

rows.title: Regular Progress
rows.titleText: You are still a regular and climbing the Tower. The options below determine your status as a Regular. The higher the rank, the more options you have available for your location setting later. Your rank will also correlate to your general strength and level of abilities.

objects.title: F-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have begun their climb on the Second Floor. This rank isn't official until the Floor's tests are successfully passed. Failing the tests of a Floor while an F-Rank Regular will cause you to lose your position as a Regular and the right t climb the Tower.

objects.title: E-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have passed the tests of the 20th Floor earn this rank. Regulars of this rank gain the security in being able to fail subsequent tests without losing the right to climb the Tower.

objects.title: D-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have pass the tests of the 30th Floor.

objects.title: C-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have passed the C-Rank Regular Test somewhere between floors 49 and 51.

objects.title: B-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have passed the B-Rank Regular Test somewhere between Floors 78 and 82.

objects.title: A-Rank
objects.text: Regulars that have passed the A-Rank Regular Test somewhere between Floors 117 and 123.

objects.title: Sponsored
objects.text: The Great Families or Special Families may sponsor special Regulars, affording them support and resources out of reach of the common Regular. However this may result in having to meddle in affairs on behalf of a sponsoring family to work around Rankers being unable to interfere in the progress of a Regular's climb.

rows.title: Ranker Progress
rows.titleText:
Congratulation, you have climbed to the 134th Floor and passed its tests. The Ranker Administration Office has officially given you a rank. Your rank represents a combination of your power, recognition, and influence. While it's possible for one to achieve a higher rank with just the latter two metrics, it is safest to assume that a higher rank implies a stronger Ranker.

There are around 100,000 Rankers in the Tower. Your Rank will indicate where you fall within this number of other Rankers. Rankers are considered to be Advanced Rankers once they reach a rank of 10,000 or less, and represent the top 10% of all Rankers. High Rankers represent the top 1% of all Rankers, and thus hold ranks 1,000 or less.

Your Rank is not fixed and can change through out your life time for any number of reasons.

objects.title: Common Ranker
objects.text: You fall within the most common set of Rankers encountered in the Tower. While there may not be too much special about you compared to another Ranker, you outclass nearly all Regulars in all capacities.

objects.title: Advanced Ranker
objects.text: You have reached elite status as a Ranker. Few will find the ability to best you in whatever you choose to specialize in. Only other Advanced Rankers or High Rankers will pose much threat to you; Regulars certainly won't.

objects.title: High Ranker
objects.text: You have reached the point that some consider you a god among gods. To other Rankers your presence will be comparable to a calamity. As a High Ranker, you also are able to become the Ruler of a Floor, should a vacancy appear.

objects.title: Blue Hole
objects.text: The term Blue Hole is given to High Rankers who have been inactive for such a long period of time that the Ranker Administration Office no longer knows of their status. It is unknown if they are still alive or dead, and their true influence and power is hard to measure. Whatever rank you choose will represent the rank you held before you became a Blue Hole.

defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
